<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Learning JavaScript</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('../partials/header') %>
    <h1><%= post.title %></h1>
     
    <p>Learning JavaScript (JS) is an essential step for anyone aspiring to become a web developer.
     It is the backbone of modern web development, bringing interactivity, logic, and functionality
     to websites. JavaScript allows developers to make web pages dynamic â€” responding to user actions, 
     updating content instantly, and communicating with servers without reloading the page. It is also 
     the only programming language that runs natively in all web browsers, making it a universal skill. 
     Beyond the browser, JavaScript powers back-end development through Node.js, and frameworks like React
    , Angular, and Vue make it even more powerful for building complex user interfaces. By learning 
    JavaScript, you open the door to full-stack development, creativity, and endless career opportunities
     in the tech industry.</p>
    

    <section class="comment-section">
    <h3>Leave a Comment</h3>
    <form action="/pages/<%= post.id %>/comment" method="POST" class="comment-form">
        <div>
            <label for="name">Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
        </div>
        <div>
            <label for="comment">Comment:</label>
            <textarea id="comment" name="comment" rows="4" required></textarea>
        </div>
        <button type="submit">Post Comment</button>
    </form>

    <% if (comments && comments.length > 0) { %>
        <div class="comments-display">
            <h4>Comments:</h4>
            <ul>
                <% comments.forEach(c => { %>
                    <li><strong><%= c.name %>:</strong> <%= c.comment %></li>
                <% }); %>
            </ul>
        </div>
    <% } %>
  </section>
    
     
    <!-- footer -->
    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>